When Txiki Begiristain made his way out of the draw hall in Nyon, Manchester City’s director of football wondered out loud why he bothered to make the short hop to Switzerland.

For Manuel Pellegrini’s team to go deep into the Champions League, City must overcome one of the most feared forward lines in the history of the game. Again.

They were beaten, well beaten as it happens, over two legs by the brilliance of Lionel Messi and his Barcelona team at this stage of the competition last season.

 

