The draw has thrown up some intriguing clashes and Arsenal will fancy their chances of progressing to the next phase after successfully avoiding one of the giants of European football. Monaco is where Arsene Wenger really got going as a coach, winning the French league in 1988 and he will return to the Stade Louis II to face his former club.

City are certainly going about it the hard way in Europe after Sergio Aguero’s remarkable hat-trick against Bayern Munich and their dramatic win in Rome.

They will play at the Etihad first and then travel to the Nou Camp to face Luis Enrique’s side. That tie is three weeks later as the last-16 draw is so strung out.

